                    <span class="level-badge">LEVEL 2</span>
                </h2>

                <div class="story-box">
                    <p><strong>üìà The Rise of Buy Now, Pay Later</strong></p>
                    <p>The BNPL industry has experienced <span class="highlight">explosive growth</span> in recent years. Transaction volume has multiplied <strong>20 times</strong> since <strong>2019</strong>, representing a dramatic shift in consumer payment preferences.</p>
                    
                    <p>Major providers typically charge merchants as much as <strong>5%</strong> of the transaction value, while <span class="highlight">90-plus percent</span> of their income comes from merchants rather than consumers. Affirm reports that about <strong>20%</strong> of their business today is 0% interest, while <strong>80%</strong> carries interest charges.</p>
                    
                    <p>However, there are growing concerns about <span class="highlight">consumer debt</span>. A LendingTree survey found that <strong>41%</strong> of BNPL users paid late in the past year, up from <strong>34%</strong> the year before. Additionally, <strong>25%</strong> of customers have used BNPL for groceries, up from <strong>14%</strong> in 2024.</p>
                </div>

